# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# Format: CVE-ID (one per line), optional comments prefixed with #
#
# CVE-2024-35515: sqlitedict insecure deserialization
# Affected: sqlitedict ≤2.1.0 (latest on PyPI as of 2025-06)
# Source: transitive dependency via lm-eval[api] (benchmark optional extra)
# Status: NO FIXED VERSION exists upstream; sqlitedict 2.1.0 is the latest release
# Context: lm-eval uses sqlitedict for SQLite-backed caching of benchmark results.
#          Headroom does NOT import sqlitedict directly; it only spawns lm-eval
#          subprocess during optional benchmark runs. The vulnerable deserialization
#          path requires crafted malicious SQLite content passed to PickledDict,
#          which is not attacker-controllable in headroom's usage pattern.
# Ref: https://cveawg.mitre.org/api/cve/CVE-2024-35515
CVE-2024-35515
